    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 2 SPEED REAR AXLES: SPICER - INSTALL - SUN GEAR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SUN GEAR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install sun gear retainer plate
                <emph type="bold">with chamfered teeth facing out</emph>
                and four bolts. Tighten bolts to:
            </para>
            <para>220 to 250 ft-lbs. (298 to 339 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the sun gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide shift fork into carrier housing and position on sun gear. Install shift fork shaft
                through hole in carrier housing and shift fork.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">New Style:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Insert and tighten set screw to 50 to 70 ft-lbs. (68 to 95 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Old Style:</emph>
            Install shift fork shaft retainer clip. Fill the shift fork shaft holes with RTV sealant.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the shift fork seal and spring to the dimension shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401533">Figure 33</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401533" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401533" filename="../figg14/G1401533.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Shift Fork Seal &#38; Spring Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
